headline: Ukraine's justice and energy ministers resign over corruption case
description: Anti-corruption prosecutors alleged that Justice Minister German Galushchenko received 'personal benefits' from a $100 million kickback scheme in the energy sector. Energy Minister Svitlana Grynchuk, who is not known to have been charged in the case, also said she was resigning.

headline: Nicolas Sarkozy leaves jail under strict judicial supervision
description: The former president cannot leave France and is prohibited from contacting any of the 17 individuals associated with the investigation. The court also barred him from meeting with any senior official with access to confidential information.

headline: The new malaise of civilization: When words, truth and reality fall apart
description: The proliferation of wars, increase in mental health disorders, devaluation of speech, and loss of connection to reality are troubling signs of the tipping point our societies are facing. Nearly a century ago, Freud identified a malaise that resonates with what we are going through today.
